name: Sunburn
wikiSummary: "Sunburn" is the fourth single by English alternative rock band Muse, and the fourth from their debut album, Showbiz. It was released on 7" vinyl—backed with a live acoustic version of the song—and double CD—backed with "Ashamed", a live version of the song, "Yes Please" and a live version of "Uno"—on 21 February 2000 and reached #22 in the UK Singles Chart[1]—an improvement of 21 positions on "Muscle Museum".
wikiText:
"Sunburn" is the fourth single by English alternative rock band Muse, and the fourth from their debut album, Showbiz. It was released on 7" vinyl—backed with a live acoustic version of the song—and double CD—backed with "Ashamed", a live version of the song, "Yes Please" and a live version of "Uno"—on 21 February 2000 and reached #22 in the UK Singles Chart[1]—an improvement of 21 positions on "Muscle Museum".
